para_trans: Terms and Conditions: -
1) The procedure prescribed under the financial rules and various regulations should be followed while drawing from the funds disbursed.
2) Immediate action should be taken to pay the funds disbursed to the relevant agencies.

3) In case of future detection of violation of the Terms and Conditions of the Regional Tourism Development Plan Government Decision, dated 4th November, 2010, the entire amount disbursed will be recovered with interest.
4) Care should be taken to ensure that the expenditure does not exceed the sanctioned subsidy under any circumstances.
Expenditure in excess of the sanctioned grant shall be the responsibility of the District Collector concerned and no additional grant shall be made available against the excess cost.

para_trans: 5) Plaques should be put up at the workplace stating that the work was done under the Regional Tourism Development Scheme.

6) Every scheme in respect of which funds are being made available shall require the approval of the competent administrator and the financial authority in accordance with the return of the financial authority.
7) In cases of proposed works of roads, it will be mandatory to follow the rules of the Public Works Department.
8) Ensure that the said provision is not used for non-plan work (maintenance / repair etc.).

9) It shall be mandatory to obtain a No Objection Certificate from the said Devasthan / Institution in respect of such works and other works which are to be carried out at the site of the Devasthan / Institute. Also, on completion of such work, it will be mandatory for the Collector to enter into an agreement with the concerned Devasthan / Institution regarding the maintenance / repair to be carried out by the concerned institution. The agreement should include a condition that it should be noted that no further funding will be made available by the government for such maintenance repairs. The agreement should also include a condition that all facilities and tourist spots created by the work will be open to all citizens.

10) The Directorate of Tourism shall submit to the Government by the 10th of every month, without fail, the physical progress of the works to be done out of the expenditure from the Fund and the monthly statements of the expenditure from the Fund.

11) Undistributed funds are being distributed to the works in this Government decision and the Collector should distribute the funds only after ensuring that the work is not completed from any other scheme / fund. If the sanctioned work has been completed from any other scheme / fund, appropriate action should be taken against the concerned for ATA and irregularity in return of funds disbursed to the government for the concerned work.
12) The funds being made available should be disbursed to the concerned system only after verifying the quality of work done so far before disbursing the funds to the concerned system.

13) Certified reports (including photographs) on the quality of work and the current status of work should be submitted to the government by the Directorate of Tourism within 1 month after a physical inspection of the work by a quality control system.
14) The utilization certificate regarding the fund should be submitted to the government through the Directorate of Tourism without fail.
15) After the completion of the work, the management of the work and other ancillary works shall be the responsibility of the implementing agency and the concerned agencies.
